title: FA pair bound for sectionals
text:
FA pair bound for sectionals 
MILTON — The Fort Atkinson girls’ golf team had two sectional qualifiers in the WIAA Division 1 Milton Regional at Oak Ridge Golf Course on Thursday. 
Senior Maile Aalto and sophomore Kaitlyn Schneider qualified with a 102 and 103 respectively, despite the Blackhawks finishing sixth out of seven as a team with a score of 436. 
“We talked before the meet today about every stroke meaning something important, that you never throw a stroke away. It was pretty evident in a lot of ways when everything was done,” said Fort head coach Jerry Shoup. 
Host Milton won the regional with a 343 while Janesville Parker, Janesville Craig and Badger all qualified as a team. 
Milton’s Mia Seeman won the event, shooting an 80. 
Despite Aalto and Schneider qualifiying for Fort, senior Nikki Bertrucci came up just short. Bertucci shot a 104, just one stroke short of tying Schneider. 
Shoup said a couple three and four putts, along with some tough chips hurt Bertucci throughout the day. 
Senior Mikayla Sullivan and freshman Miranda Aalto finished out the scoring group for Fort, shooting a 127 and a 131 respectively. 
Beloit Memorial’s Chloe Day shot a 96 and Elkhorn Area’s Jessica Barrett shot a 101 to claim the other two individual qualifiers spots in the regional. 
Maile Aalto and Schneider will take part in the Mukwonago Sectional, at 8:40 a.m. on Tuesday at the Edgewood Golf Club.
